15 "20-2-21.
16 (a) As used in this Code section, the term:
17 (1) 'Department' means the Georgia Department of Education.
18 (2) 'Local education agency' shall have the same meaning as set forth in Code
19 Section 20-2-167.1.
20 (3) 'Study' or 'impact study' means the impact study provided for in this Code section.
21 (b) The department shall complete an impact study within 90 days of any action by any
22 branch of the federal government that results in a reduction of more than 20 percent in the
23 scope, workforce, or budget of the United States Department of Education; provided,
24 however, that, if such federal action occurs prior to the effective date of this Act, such
25 study shall be completed within 90 days of the effective date of this Act. Such study shall
26 assess the impact of such federal action on public primary and secondary education in this
27 state and shall include, but shall not be limited to, the potential effects of such federal
28 action on:
29 (1) Each local education agency and each public primary and secondary school in this
30 state, including, but not limited to, effects related to funding, staffing, resources, and
31 school operations; and
32 (2) Students, including, but not limited to, academic performance and access to
33 programs.
34 (c) The department shall be authorized to contract with a nonpartisan independent entity
35 with expertise in education policy and finance to conduct the study.
36 (d) The department shall prepare a report on the findings of the study, which shall be
37 provided to each local education agency and shall be made available on the department's
38 website in a format that is accessible and understandable by the public."
39 SECTION 3.
40 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
